SIMPLE: heterodromous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heterodromous
<hw>Het`er*od"ro*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hetero-</ets> + Gr. <?/ to run.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having spirals of changing direction.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>Moving in opposite directions; --
said of a lever, pulley, etc., in which the resistance and the actuating
force are on opposite sides of the fulcrum or axis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heteroecious</ent>⟦br⟧
